# Slice OPS.5 — Trivy vulnerability suppressions.
#
# One CVE id per line to suppress a triaged finding. Every entry MUST carry a
# comment: who triaged it, when, and why it's acceptable (not exploitable in our
# context / no fix available / accepted risk). The pre-launch go-live gate is:
# review the latest `trivy-*` SARIF artifact and confirm no un-triaged
# HIGH/CRITICAL-fixable finding remains outside this file.
#
# Format:
#   CVE-2024-XXXXX   # 2026-07-10 <name>: <reason>
#
# (empty — populate during the pre-launch Trivy triage)
